You'll need Qt4 (>= 4.3?)

qmake piQtureGLide.pro && make
sudo install piQtureGLide /usr/local/bin

the diashow script thing is there for historic reasons and may be polishe or removed in further releases

you can install the kgldiashow.xml dtd to have a better syntax highlightning for the diashow scrip language
file goes to $KDEDIR/share/apps/katepart/syntax - your local $KDEDIR is usually ~/.kde
